insert  into `wyzeup_scenarios`(`scenario_id`,`scenario_name`,`scenario_desc`,`scenario_image`,`scenario_status`,`scenario_isdeleted`) values (1,'Sweets','Tom is walking home from school with his older sister Chloe.  As usual they stop at the shop to buy an apple.  Tom sees a man a few shops away watching the children; he has some shopping with him. \r\n\r\nChloe and Tom eat their apples but it has been a long time since lunch and Tom is still hungry.  Just then the man comes up to Chloe and asks her the way to the Park; she decides there is no harm in telling him','1_img-child.jpg',1,1),(2,'Drugs','Shakir was waiting for his friends after school near the school gates.  There are several young men with cars hanging around laughing with the girls and mucking about. After a while one of them came over and started talking with Shakir about what school was like.  Shakir was not sure that he liked the young man and didn√É¬¢√¢‚Äö¬¨√¢‚Äû¬¢t really want to talk to him.','2_image1.jpg',1,1),(3,'Building site','Building site descripfdsufh v','',1,1),(4,'For testing Scenario','Wyze-up is a web-based, interactive program to help educate children by growing their awareness of what is a danger sign or a potentially unsafe situation. \r\n\r\nThe site provides a number of different scenarios covering typical real-life situations and is designed to complement teaching of the PSHCE curriculum. Each scenario is described in language that children between five and seven years old will easily understand and is presented on a simulated games-style console. \r\n\r\nThe program is available to schools on an annual, unlimited user licensed basis for only √Ç¬£19:95 per annum. E-learning credits may also be used if preferred.\r\n\r\nFor each scenario, up to five situation developments are described. After reading each development the child has to decide whether the decision that the character has taken is Wyze or Un-wyze. Having made the decision, the next development in the scenario can be selected. Correctly identifying the Wyze or Un-wyze decisions by the character moves a graduated progress bar.','4_11.jpg',1,1),(5,'Strangers','Strangers','',1,1),(6,'Strangers','Chloe was right to be very careful. It is best not to talk to strangers. Never, ever go anywhere with a stanger no matter what they may say or offer you.','',1,0),(7,'Drugs','Don\\\'t ever take any pills or powders from anyone. Drugs can easily kill you and are very dangerous. Even drugs that look like sweets are dangerous. Don\\\'t ever be tempted whatever anyone may tell you.','',1,0),(8,'Playing outside','Building sites and other places that have fences around them can be very dangerous. You can get in to trouble or even hurt yourself if you play where you shouldn\\\'t. Be careful where you play.','',1,0),(9,'Out shopping','Always be careful when you are in busy places. It is very easy to get lost so don\\\'t wander away from whoever is looking after you. If you do ever get lost try and find someone in a uniform who can help you. Just like Alice did.','',1,0),(10,'The Seaside','Anah was right to keep a look out for the tide. The seaside can be great fun as long as you are sensible and never go too far from who ever is looking afer you.','',1,0),(11,'At the park','Playgrounds are great fun but doing silly things can be dangerous. If you or a friend ever have an accident playing always try and find a grown up nearby who can help. Shouting \\\"Help!\\\" will let people know you need them quickly.','',1,0),(12,'Missing dog','It was kind to help the man look for his dog but Jemma and Tim were right not to go in to the woods to look for him. After all the man was still a stranger and Jemma and Tim knew that they must never go anywhere with a stranger.','',1,0),(13,'Medicines','Yakir did the right thing by calling 999. Very soon an ambulance and a doctor arrived to make his Mum better. If you find someone who looks very ill or isn\\\'t moving call 999.','',1,0),(14,'Down by the river','They were